<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.188179>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Macrobiotus creber sp. nov. A, bucco-pharyngeal apparatus (holotype); B, claws of the first three pairs of legs (holotype) (the arrow indicates the cuticular bar); C, egg; D, E, F, details of eggs. Scale bar = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/188179/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.188181>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Macrobiotus perfidus sp. nov. A, some cuticular tubercles (arrows) are in evidence (holotype); B, buccopharyngeal apparatus (holotype); C, claws of the first and second pairs of legs (holotype); D, claws of the fourth pair of legs (holotype); E, F, details of the egg. Scale bar = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/188181/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

